news.title: Reserve Bank of India cuts repo rate by 50 bps
news.para: The Monetary Policy Committee (MPC), which consists of three RBI officials and three external members, cut the repo rate to 5.50%. It has now cut rates by 100 basis points in 2025, starting with a quarter-point reduction in February, its first cut since May 2020. It made a similar-sized cut in April.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to take action as cheque bounce cases rise in property tax payments
news.para: A senior official from the property tax department confirmed that in March 2025 alone, 780 cheques amounting to Rs 10.15 crore were dishonoured—the highest number recorded in recent years.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body concludes probe in property tax scam
news.para: Well-placed sources said the authorities are planning to take action against the violators, both within and outside MC. The MC employee, who is a suspect, is reportedly claiming innocence. The suspect has also offered to get a narco test done, the sources said.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body identifies 527 buildings as ‘dangerous’
news.para: "Continued occupation of such structures poses significant risks, and the corporation will not be liable for any resulting incidents," said NMMC commissioner Kailas Shinde.

news.title: Odisha RERA directs developers to update project details on new website
news.para: The recently launched website is a comprehensive platform for homebuyers to visit and easily get the latest information about the projects in which they invested their hard-earned money.

news.title: Odisha HC junks plea against LIC over public auction of cancelled flat allotments
news.para: The petition sought HC's intervention, alleging that LIC is now attempting to profit from the same flats by hiking its cost to Rs 80.54 lakh from the earlier Rs 58.10 lakh, which amounts to arbitrary and exploitative conduct unbecoming of a state entity.

news.title: Maradu municipality hands over flat keys to housing scheme beneficiaries
news.para: The complex, with an area of 6,856 sq ft, consists of eight flats — each with a living room, kitchen, balcony and two bedrooms with attached bathrooms — providing modern housing facilities for beneficiary families.

news.title: SC asks HC to seek status on landlord-tenant case pendency
news.para: "When it comes to landlord-tenant disputes, there is an angle of being deprived of the enjoyment of the property and also the monetary benefits that accrue from owning such property,'' the Supreme Court has said.

news.title: State readying sand erosion management plan: Goa CM
news.para: Sawant urged the people to strictly implement the single-use plastic ban in the state from World Environment Day (June 5). He said Goa is the number one state for working towards preserving biodiversity.

news.title: Lucknow development body seeks public feedback for new apartment projects
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar said the authority aims to provide quality housing equipped with basic and modern facilities to people across all income groups.

news.title: Noida: Land not acquired but housing scheme launched, three GNIDA officials suspended
news.para: ​The officials issued allotment letters for 9,600sqm in Patwari village, despite only 1,600sqm being legally acquired from farmers, prompting Allahabad High Court to call the process "arbitrary and reckless".

news.title: Goa's town planning department approves conversion of one lakh sq meter green land
news.para: Of the 1 lakh sqm that was put up for conversion, nearly 69,129sqm falls in Pernem’s Parcem village. The entire tranche of land was converted for residential housing.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh set to sign fresh lease with third-party developers for 13 Sports City projects
news.para: Officials said these 13 projects involved 13,132 buyers across sectors 25 and 19. According to them, executing the fresh deeds had become mandatory following the HC's decision, which nullified every reference to JAL in previous agreements.

news.title: FIR against colonizers for fraud, illegal construction in Ujjain
news.para: Inspector Reema Yadav said that the EOW investigated Gauri Nandan Complex Colony on land survey number 3268/3 in Chintaman Jawasia village, Ujjain and Dashrath Nandan Colony on land survey number 138/2 in the same village.

news.title: MahaRERA revises project certificate format to provide detailed information to homebuyers
news.para: MahaRERA officials said the aim is to ensure that all key project details — already mandated to be displayed at the project site, in advertisements, and on the MahaRERA website — are now clearly mentioned on the registration certificate as well.

news.title: Gucci owner Kering in talks to sell stake in $1 billion Fifth Avenue property: Sources
news.para: Kering, controlled by family of CEO Francois-Henri Pinault, bought 715-717 Fifth Avenue in January 2024 for $963 million to secure a top retail location in one of the world's most popular shopping streets.

news.title: Blackstone among bidders for $800 million commercial property in Paris: Sources
news.para: The CityQuartier Trocadero building is in a prime location in the 16th arrondissement near the Arc de Triomphe and was put up for sale by the owner, Germany's Union Investment, in March.

news.title: UK's Unite Group bids $976 million for Empiric Student Property
news.para: Under the possible offer, shareholders of real estate investment trust Empiric would receive 30 pence in cash and 0.09 new Unite shares for each Empiric share held, for an implied value of 107 pence per share, the groups said.

news.title: Apple India leases 12,616 sq ft space at Sky City Mall in Mumbai
news.para: Premium mobile device maker Apple India has leased this space from Incline Realty for a period of 10 years and 10 months. The rent free period is 10 months.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body asks PU, PGI to clear ₹93 crore in property tax dues
news.para: ​Following extensive reconciliation efforts, the civic body, which has long struggled to make top property tax payers clear their dues running into crores, has raised fresh demands with Panjab University and PGI, Chandigarh, to pay up their property tax and service charges, pending for years.
